name: Muttom Fishing Harbour
description: A harbor is a sheltered body of water where ships, boats, and barges can be docked. Harbor and port are often used interchangeably when referring to a man-made facility that is used for the loading & unloading of vessels, as well as managing disembarkment & embarkment of passengers. Ports are often characterized by the presence of one or more harbors which allow for a safe and secure docking of ships.
location: 48CM+Q2Q, Muttom East Break Water, Ganapathipuram, Tamil Nadu 629202
